extendedInfo.description: Dog owners are always concern with what is safe to feed their dogs. This handy application helps dogs owner everywhere to answer such questions and provides descriptions on why certain food or plants are safe or unsafe for dogs to eat. This application can prevent the unfortunate trips to the vet, or worst, the lost of our furry faithful companions. Before buying or giving their dogs some chocolate chips cookies, dog owners can quickly do a search with this application to see if chocolate is safe for their dogs. This application will be able to clearly inform them that chocolate is unsafe for their dogs with a display of a sick dog on the screen and description on why and how sick the dogs can get.

reviews.title: Windows?
reviews.comment: I love your app and use it constantly, however I am switching to a Windows phone. Do you have plans to make it available on Windows? -BlueEyez4228
reviews.author: Tanya Simpson

reviews.title: Useless
reviews.comment: I feed my dog a raw diet of different meats with a vegetable mix, for which, I have researched  numerous sources. This app is often completely wrong and when searching something common, like red pepper or kelp, brings up a bunch of obscure plants that nobody would consider feeding their dog because they have no idea what it is. For your dog\'s sake find a book on the subject.
reviews.author: Glenn Thomander
